# Analysis of Main Target Image

The main target image shows two separate structures:

## Structure 1 (Left Structure):
- This is a structure with 4 blocks total, arranged in 2 layers
- Bottom layer: 3 orange cylindrical blocks (pillars) arranged to form an archway
- Top layer: 1 yellow rectangular block placed horizontally on top of the orange cylinders
- On top of the yellow block: 1 orange triangular/wedge-shaped block

## Structure 2 (Right Structure):
- This is a structure with 6 blocks total, arranged in 3 layers
- Bottom layer: 1 green rectangular block placed horizontally 
- Middle layer: 3 yellow rectangular blocks arranged to form a U-shape (2 vertical sides and 1 horizontal connecting piece)
- Inside the U-shape: 1 red cube
- Top layer: 1 green rectangular block placed horizontally on top of the yellow vertical blocks

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

## For Structure 1 (Left):
- 3× Block #9 (orange vertical cylinders)
- 1× Block #6 (yellow horizontal rectangular block)
- 1× Block #12 (orange triangular/wedge block)

## For Structure 2 (Right):
- 2× Block #4 (green horizontal rectangular blocks)
- 2× Block #7 (yellow vertical rectangular blocks)
- 1× Block #6 (yellow horizontal rectangular block)
- 1× Block #2 (red cube)

# Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 9
   Step2: Move block with index 9
   Step3: Move block with index 9
   Step4: Move block with index 6
   Step5: Move block with index 12
   Step6: Move block with index 4
   Step7: Move block with index 7
   Step8: Move block with index 7
   Step9: Move block with index 6
   Step10: Move block with index 2
   Step11: Move block with index 4
}
```

This assembly order first builds the left structure from bottom to top (steps 1-5), then builds the right structure from bottom to top (steps 6-11).
